com.martensigwart.fakeload

Interface FakeLoad

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<FakeLoad>

    public interface FakeLoad
extends Iterable<FakeLoad>
    Represents the main API for the FakeLoad Library. With instances of this type clients decide what kinds of system loads they want to generate and for how long.

    Clients can specify what kind of load (e.g. CPU, RAM, …), how much of it (e.g. 80%, 1024MB, …) and for how long a specific load (e.g. 10 s, 100 ms, …) is being simulated. Also, a fake load can itself consist of other FakeLoad instances thus giving the client the possibility to create complex patterns of system load instructions.

    Note: All setter methods return a FakeLoad instance themselves, thus allowing a kind of fluent interface like this: 

      FakeLoad fakeload = FakeLoads.create()
      .lasting(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)
      .withCpu(30)
      .withMemory(300, MemoryUnit.MB)
      .withDiskInput(10, MemoryUnit.KB)
      .withDiskOutput(20, MemoryUnit.MB);
    Depending on whether the underlying FakeLoad implementation is mutable or immutable these methods can either merely set specific load parameters or return a completely new FakeLoad instance containing the new parameters, respectively.
    Since:
    1.8
    Author:
    Marten Sigwart
    See Also:
    FakeLoads, FakeLoadExecutor
